# Example SMTP environment variables for local testing and deployment
# Replace values with your SMTP provider credentials (Mailtrap, SendGrid, Mailgun, etc.)

# Required
SMTP_HOST=smtp.mailtrap.io
SMTP_PORT=2525
SMTP_USER=your_mailtrap_user
SMTP_PASS=your_mailtrap_pass

# Optional
SMTP_SECURE=false   # true for port 465, false otherwise
SENDER_EMAIL=no-reply@yourdomain.com
RECEIVER_EMAIL=devanshnegi88@gmail.com

# FormSubmit / Frontend form recipient (used by ContactForm)
# Set this to the email where you want to receive messages via FormSubmit
VITE_CONTACT_EMAIL=devanshnegi88@gmail.com

# Notes:
# - For local testing of serverless functions, use `npx vercel dev` and ensure these vars are set in your environment
# - For production, set the env vars in your hosting provider (Vercel/Netlify) dashboard, not in git

# To use FormSubmit (frontend AJAX):
# 1. Option A (recommended): No additional config required — FormSubmit will forward to the address you POST to.
# 2. Option B (if you want extra protection): Visit https://formsubmit.co and follow the instructions to verify your email and configure templates.

